 Port Elizabeth - The South African Police Service in Gelvandale, Port Elizabeth, are investigating an inquest docket after the body of a child was found in an open field on Sunday morning. "It is alleged that on Sunday, at approximately 09:00, a community member was walking in an open field in Malabar ext 6 next to a dam when he found a skull and upon further observation he found human bones," described police spokesperson, Capt Sandra Janse Van Rensburg. "He alerted the police , "Due to the state of decomposition, the identification of the child cannot be determined at this stage and a post mortem and DNA testing will be done to determine the identity and cause of death." Capt Janse Van Rensburg An Inquest is currently under investigation. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 